The `decodeString` function uses `atob` to convert the Base64-encoded string back to a regular string, and `decodeURIComponent` and `escape` to reverse the encoding process.

Note that the resulting encoded string will be longer than the original string, but it will be safe to share via a URL and can be easily decoded back to the original string.

